{
  "_comment": "CoW Protocol EIP-712 Order signing corpus (mainnet). Hand-built typed-data fixtures because CoW orders are signed off-chain (orderbook) and do NOT appear in Etherscan tx input. Entries 1-2 are REAL mainnet orders pulled from the CoW orderbook API (order uid in intent); entries 3,5-7 are synthetic edges (3=self-receiver receiver=0x0, 5=partiallyFillable=true + Balancer-vault balances sellTokenBalance=external/buyTokenBalance=internal, 6=native-ETH buy via BUY_ETH_ADDRESS sentinel 0xEeee..EEeE [1st-party GPv2Transfer.sol] + validTo in the past, 7=buy-kind + sellTokenBalance=internal + nonzero feeAmount). Two further entries (L5a) are REAL on-chain CoWSwapEthFlow.createOrder calldata txs (native-ETH placement) from BOTH active ethflow contracts (prod 0xba3c..eadec + v1 0x40a5..2187): rpc-type, to=ethflow, value=msg.value=sellAmount+feeAmount(decimal), data=raw createOrder calldata; sell is baked WETH (EthFlowOrder.Data has no sellToken), -> amm sign_intent_order OnchainTx. domain='Gnosis Protocol' v2, verifying_contract=GPv2Settlement 0x9008d19f58aabd9ed0d60971565aa8510560ab41, primary_type=Order. kind/sellTokenBalance/buyTokenBalance are EIP-712 'string'; the decoder hardcodes order_kind='limit' and does NOT map kind/partiallyFillable/appData/feeAmount/balances (see onboarding evidence L3). buy_min := order buyAmount (the signed minimum, NOT the trade-executed amount). NOTE entries 1-3 pin amounts as exact U256 lower-hex (equals); entries 5-7 use u256_hex_eq with decimal values (normalizes hex<->decimal, avoids the encoding gotcha) and pin valid_until via u256_hex_eq (Time serializes as a JSON number). Three further entries are REAL on-chain GPv2Settlement.setPreSignature(bytes orderUid, bool signed) calldata txs (the smart-contract-wallet order-placement path) -> amm pre_sign_intent_order: two signed=true pre-signs (commit) from distinct owners (tx 0x0f78fea7 / 0x6d83de81) + one signed=false revoke (tx 0x11b07e5e). The opaque orderUid (56B) is carried verbatim as order_hash; the bool `signed` is pinned via op=equals (JSON bool). No sell/buy/amount terms exist in this calldata (they live in the off-chain order keyed by the digest).",
